parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Transmission failure can cause the vehicle to lose power, making it difficult to control, and potentially leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle suddenly rolls in reverse with the shifter in the park position
the vehicle will not engage into gear
the transmission slips or hesitates
the transmission makes unusual noises
the vehicle jumps back unexpectedly.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Transmission recall repair issues can cause the vehicle to experience transmission problems, making it difficult to control, and potentially leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle experiences transmission problems after recall repair
the dealer is unable to honor the recall due to parts availability
the dealer is unable to properly repair the transmission
the consumer is not satisfied with the recall work done by the dealer.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the steering system can cause loss of control, making it difficult to steer the vehicle, which can lead to accidents.
symptoms: Power steering pump is leaking fluid
steering is loose
vehicle wanders on the road
steering wheel is cracked
loss of steering while driving
steering column causes vibration
steering pitman arm fails repeatedly.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the power steering pump can cause the vehicle to become inoperable, leading to accidents or stranding the driver.
symptoms: Power steering pump is leaking fluid
causing the vehicle to be inoperable.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the steering rack and pinion can cause loss of control, making it difficult to steer the vehicle, which can lead to accidents.
symptoms: Oil leaking from the rack and pinion area
rack and pinion requires replacement.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the steering column can cause loss of control, making it difficult to steer the vehicle, which can lead to accidents.
symptoms: Steering column causes vibration
problem with steering column causes vibration.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure to repair recalled components can lead to accidents or other safety issues.
symptoms: Dealer unable to repair recalled components due to lack of parts
dealer unable to repair recalled components due to dirty engine.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of the ABS brake system can cause extended stopping distances, loss of control, and accidents, especially on wet or slippery roads.
symptoms: The ABS light comes on while driving
the vehicle vibrates or bucks when applying the brakes
the brake system kicks in without pedal application
the vehicle pulls to one side
the brake pedal goes to the floor.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake master cylinder can cause the brake pedal to go to the floor, making it difficult or impossible to stop the vehicle, which can lead to accidents.
symptoms: The brake pedal goes to the floor
the vehicle is unable to stop or has extended stopping distances.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Worn or damaged brake rotors can cause the brakes to pulsate or vibrate, leading to reduced braking performance and increased stopping distances.
symptoms: Holes in front brake rotors
laminated rotors
pulsating brakes when applied.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake system can cause the brakes to fail, leading to accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: Continuous brake failure
damaging other components.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ABS wiring harness can cause the ABS system to malfunction, leading to extended stopping distances and loss of control.
symptoms: ABS wiring harness failure
repeated failures.
